                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0131DMB">Baʿātti Qǝddus Mikāʾel</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate when="1937">According to the colophon, the Ms.
                        was written during the time of the Italian occupation (zamana mangǝśtomu
                        Romāwǝyān), on 18 Miyāzyā 1929 year of mercy (= 26 April 1937
                        A.D.).</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Ownership history: according to the colophon, the Ms. was
                     donated by <persName role="patron" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12835Barhe">lǝğ Barhe</persName> (of) Baʿātti, whose baptismal name was Gabra Ḥǝywat. The
                     latter name has been inserted into supplication formulas (<locus target="#15vb">15vb</locus>, 18rb, 21vb etc.); in addition, other names are mentioned like
                     Walatta Māryām (<locus target="#10va">10va</locus>, 12va, 18ra etc.), Walatta
                     Ṣādǝqān (e.g., <locus target="#16ra">16ra</locus>, 59vb, 73rb), Gabra Mikāʾel
                     (e.g., <locus target="#19rb">19rb</locus>, 55vb, 77vb), Walatta Kidān (e.g.,
                     <locus target="#19rb">19rb</locus>, 49rb, 52ra), Walda Śǝllāse (<locus target="#23ra">23ra</locus>, 25va, 27ra etc.).</provenance>
